Maybe somebody can give me some suggestions on how to really challenge
myself in Frontier.

I used to jump around the old Lave system, particularly between Reorte
and Zaonce.  With my 4MW Beam Laser equipped Cobra MK III it wasn't
even that bad.  On Reorte I sometimes get intercepted twenty, thirty
times before actually reaching the space station.  Though none of the
opponents every pose a threat.  There are occasionally some Imperial
Couriers hanging around there, but unless you do something really
stupid, those slow boats won't be able to get a shot at you.  You only
need to watch those nasty Naval Missiles.  If you forget about one of
those and accelerate time forward you are toast.

Somebody suggested Phekda as a good place, so I got myself an old
Gecko and did a few 40ly jumps to that star system. I bounced a few
times between Phekda and another planet near it... a disputed planet,
but it was plain boring out there. There was less action than on
Reorte.

Does anybody have some suggestions?  I think downgrading the ship
won't make things any more interesting.  The Cobra MK III is about the
smallest ship which can hold a 4MW beam laser.  A smaller laser only
drags out the fights for a longer period of time.  That doesn't seem
to make fights more challenging, but only increases the time until you
kill the enemy (and hence until the next promotion).  I do generally
keep 2 - 4 shields around.  I rarely get hit (mostly when I do stupid
things like using the auto pilot to aim at other ships...  hey
everybody needs a break sometimes!), but I doubt that throwing away
the shields will help much.

One thing I haven't gotten to work is to get more than one enemy on my
screen.  Somebody suggested not to use the maximum time acceleration,
but I tried that and used the next lower acceleration.  It just took
longer before the next enemy appeared, but it was still always just
_one_ enemy.  Any hints?

I also tried wiping out whole space stations. In case anybody is
interested, an easy method is to sit right by the door. Police Vipers
get released in pairs, so you just need to kill them off when they
leave. Though I don't quite yet want to make myself a WANTED pirate.
Maybe later, for now I just want to reach ELITE ranking. BTW, space
stations themselves cannot be destroyed.

Oh well, hope this is enough discussion material on this topic.  I
would like to hear some input on how to get the ultimate trip in
Frontier.  :)

Stefan

