In article MSGID, sgberg@charon.bloomington.in.us (Stefan G. Berg) says:
>One thing I haven't gotten to work is to get more than one enemy on my
>screen.  Somebody suggested not to use the maximum time acceleration,
>but I tried that and used the next lower acceleration.  It just took
>longer before the next enemy appeared, but it was still always just
>_one_ enemy.  Any hints?

Honest to God, I swear this works:

1. You arrive in a star system.
2. Pull up the Current System Map. Spin it around and zoom it so you
get a good close look at your current location (big purple dot.)
3. You're probably surrounded by a couple of other, smaller colored
dots. These are other ships, almost certainly pirates.
4. Use the autopilot icon to select the nearest one. It is somewhat
tricky to select other dots that are very close to your own dot, but
I got the hang of it after a while.
5. Go back to the main view. The HUD tells you how far away the other
ship(s) are. You can scan them with the Hyperspace Analyzer, or call
them up to see if they're really pirates.
6. Turn on your Autopilot. You begin flying towards the pirates.
7. Now you can manipulate the time compression to your heart's content.
Leave it at 4 or 5 if you're really far from the enemy, start cranking
it down when you get close. It should be at either 2 or 3 when the
"under attack" alarm siren goes off.
8. Done everything right? You should be attacked by the entire pirate group
(usually 3 ships). Sometimes, pirates really honestly do go out alone,
so you'll still have one-on-one battles, but I'd say about one-third to
one-half are groups of 3 ships.
9. And, er, that's it. It's not insanely difficult to handle, but it's
much more fun than knocking the pirates over one at a time. Repeat the
above steps for all the nearby pirates on your scanner, and once the
stellar neighborhood is cleared of evildoers, you can autopilot your
way safely to your destination insystem.

Cumbersome, yes, but better than one-on-one battles until the end of
time. I _really_ hope that combat is made more challenging in future
versions, if such exist; it should get more difficult as your Elite
rating improves, and increase in variety. Being attacked by, say,
a Tiger Trader (with active gun turrets, of course -- noticed that
even if the enemy ship has more than just the front gun mount, the
pirates never seem to use theirs? Tch tch tch...) accompanied by
a couple of fighters flying escort would be rather entertaining.

>I also tried wiping out whole space stations. In case anybody is
>interested, an easy method is to sit right by the door. Police Vipers
>get released in pairs, so you just need to kill them off when they
>leave. Though I don't quite yet want to make myself a WANTED pirate.
>Maybe later, for now I just want to reach ELITE ranking. BTW, space
>stations themselves cannot be destroyed.

You can do that if you want to rack up your kill rating... of course,
you can save wear-and-tear on your laser by just letting them ram
into each other as they emerge from the station. This has _got_ to be
fixed.

Other ships' AI in general has problems -- there are wonderful things,
like the way an assassination target will try to flee back into the
safety of an underground base, but then there are the things that make
you want to cover your eyes in shame. Like, one time I was hanging out
near a space station and decided to track a cargo ship all the way in.
He sailed in from the edge of the system, got docking permission, the
lights went on and the doors opened (I thought that was cool, that
they dock the same way you do), he flew smoothly up to the station, smacked
into the wall of the bay and blew up. *sigh*

Two conclusions:

1. Other ships in the Frontier universe have an autopilot that's just
as good as the one in your own ship!
2. Ya know, after a horrible space accident like that I would expect
the space station to shut down operations for a couple hours while
police and Red Cross ships swarm the area, and probably the local news
media too... :-)

                    I've gone to build the Supercollider.
