This is not a flame post.

Frontier Wish List (Frontier 2 perhaps?):

- AGA version:

i) real graphics: 256 colour, real faces (aliens too)
ii) able to use different monitors (ie DBLPAL)
iii) real sound: proper modules without reusing instruments
iv) more speed

- aliens... real aliens, and not just one race... millions of them
(friendly aliens, bad aliens etc.)

- who says that everybody speaks the same language? how about
interpreters/universal decoders?

- different propulsion systems (thrusters in year 3200 are a joke)
(how about a local gravitational field?)

- many different ships

- able to own multiple ships

- able to own cities/planets/systems etc.

- more interaction with your crew - ie. able to talk to them.
how about the crew actually doing something?  (ie. using the back laser?)

- better HUD (head up display):  the current one is a joke during combat

- adding components to your ship that weigh less than 1 tonne.
(eg. the automatic pilot should really be a few kilos since it's just
an addition to the on-board computer system)

- better automatic pilot (maybe 2 versions) - ie. 
i) use the main thruster to slow down the ship... 
ii) fly to different cities NOT through planets

- unknown alien aircraft that is snooping around planets perhaps?

- better military missions... full on wars maybe?

- bigger galaxy with more populated planets.

- able to view 360 degrees from inside the ship: not just front and
back views.

- hyperspace:  the only reason I have found so far for coming out of
hyperspace so far away is because you can do some combat.  Since you are
able to enter hyperspace pretty much anywhere (except planets), why are you
limited to exiting it around 10 AUs from the required planet?  Even worse
situations like Alpha Centauri where you are 200 AUs away...

Any additions/suggestions are welcome.


