Just some remarks on that. You will see, in news.groups, a lot of people
not actually interested in Frontier, but quite more interested to maintain
a concise, understandable and longer lasting namespace in netland. 

Those will, quite likely, strongly oppose an own newsgroup for a recently
published arcade type video game. (Please don't argue on that classification 
- I try to explain how others might see that). And you should realize, that 
strong  opposition could, in many cases, mean failure of the group creation.
I would even vote against it myself.

So I suggest setting up this group in the alt.* hierarchy, where it, 
admittedly, might suffer from a slightly worse distribution, but
has, due to the lack restrictions there, good chances to get created.

The ususal way to create a group in alt.* is to post a suggestion to
alt.config (?) and discuss the name there. Then you or someone you ask 
about it (maybe one of the folks in alt.config) can create the group.
My personal suggestion would be alt.games.frontier.

If you really insist on the whole process to establish a "big seven" 
group, then I suggest not only thorough reading of the "how to create
a new USENET newsgroup" document, but also the "primer" published
on that subject by some news.groups regulars, which contains lots of
dos and don'ts you don't find anywhere else.

Regards

