The relationship between hyper and interplanetary drives doesn't seem to be 
properly defined in Frontier. A hyperdrive is said to incorporate an interplanetary
drive, and one of the Class 6 variety weighs 250t. Yet, when lack of servicing 
reduced my drive to 250t of rubbish, my interplanetary drive still got me to the
nearest space station. Frontier has rules, but they are not bound by logic!!!

Also, it seems Mr Braben inserted code to prevent *removing* of drives from Imperial
ships but not *fitting*, since the "drive already fitted" code should (oops!) handle 
that. For example, I tried removing the Class 7 drive in my Trader, to see if I had
somehow permanently removed the interchange restriction, but it wouldn't budge.
The object that 2 seconds earlier I had fitted to my ship, magically became an
"integral part" of it. There is *NOTHING* intentional on Mr B's part about this I'm 
afraid, it's just another loop-hole. It is however an example of the more pleasant
variety of loop-hole, the beneficial kind!!!


