I seem to be one of the few people in Australia with Frontier, but
unfortunately it is only Version 1.00.

Despite the fact that there are numerous know bugs in the game, I have only
seen the following:  Bulletin Board, Crashing AutoPilot, and the following
which I haven't seen mentioned before:

Select the star map (F2), not move to cursor to another star system, get
info on it (F6).  Now reset the cursor to where you are now (C), now get
info again (F6) and you get the details from where you were, not where you
are.  The fix is to move the cursor away manually and then back again.

I have also discovered a "feature" not mentioned in the manual.  Select the
orbital map of any system (F2 F2).  Select one of the objects (planet, star,
etc) now double click on the zoom in gadget (F7).  It automatically zooms
all the way into the object.

In the same orbital map I can see a small blue dot.  It moves around when
you reorient the map with the mouse, but it doesn't seem to be in a constant
place.  I originally thought that it was my current ship position, but it
doesn't actually seem to be that.  The manual makes no mention of it.  Any
ideas?

Has anyone heard officially (or otherwise) where it is possible to get
updates to the latest version?

Early in the game you can make lots of cash doing the Barnard's Star -> Sol
route with robots and luxuries, but it is also possible to make a lot doing
the Faerce -> Vequve route taking military missions one way (upto 12 at a
time) and slaves the other.

I currently am running an Asp Explorer and am thinking of trading up to an
Imperial Courier.  Is it worth it?


Thanks,
