I have been playing Amiga Frontier for about a week now, and dispite the
bugs it is a great game.

A friend of mine has just bought it for the PC, and I thought that I would
do a quick comparison:

-  The box and manuals are almost identical.  The only difference is that
   the quick-start guide has a slightly different arrangement of icons on
   the last page.  They both come on two DSDD disks.

-  The PC version uses a 256 colour screen mode, and the Amiga uses a 16
   colour mode.  This doesn't actually make very much difference.  As people
   have said the PC version does texture mapping, and it looks *horrible*.
   I turned it off immediately.

-  The Amiga has square pixels, and VGA has 4x3 pixels, so on the PC all the
   planets look slightly egg-shaped.

-  Neither game allows you to exit.

-  The saved commanders between Amiga v1.00 and PC v2.00 are not compatible.

-  Ceimiss sells Precious metals for -3000 on both.

-  The game "feels" nicer on the Amiga, but my 386DX/40 runs it much smoother
   than my 68000/14 (which is not really a surprise).

-  The Amiga version cost $A70, and the PC version was $A90!


It's a great game on either platform.  Has anyone seen (or even heard of)
the Atari ST version?


Phil.

