In article <2d0262f1@p1.f114.n200.z2.ct.se> andreas_jelvemark@p1.f114.n200.z2.ct.se (Andreas Jelvemark) writes:

>How can you fly to a planet without the autopilot? (It must be possible.... )

Possible, yes.  Not even particularly difficult.  Just target the port you want
just as you normally would with autopilot.  Make certain you have f10 on so you
can see the names of things and targetting tunnels from the options menu.  Then
just fly down the 'tunnel' until you get where you are going.  Be careful about
your speed though.  Slow down as you get closer, and when you actually go in to
dock you want to be down in the km/HOUR (not second) range.  Then request
docking clearance and put your landing gear down.

Might take a little practice if you aren't used to manual control, but it's
fairly easy... and probably safer than letting that damnfool autopilot do the
docking in any case.  :)
