A STORY FROM FRONTIER


As I came out of hyperspace, I noticed the typical imperial navy squabble on the
radio. Among the names mentioned, where those of 'Imperial Cruiser Executor' and
'Fort Roxxan'. My triggerfinger twitched, but I decided to check out how many
there were before I shot them down.

And I had passengers aboard. But Ilika Mansjon, a female b-star of dream-movies,
was quite bitchy towards me and the crew since my ship was three weeks behind
schedule. My ship had run into some rather cheeky pirates in the last system,
even though my 2000-ton Panther Clipper bristled with guns and rockets, the 20-ton
light pirate cruiser pilot bluntly said 'Ha! Surrender or die!'. He lived some
twenty seconds more. And we had to assasinate a mafia topgun, he was reduced to
space-debris within seconds. The plasma accelerator is a mean machine. So no
wonder we were late.

So, after some three days, we arrived at the spacestation. Ohjoy, two imperial
medium cruiser (that big thing in the intro), floated innocently twenty
kilometers from the spacestation, which was of the old hexagon type. 

I dropped of Ilika, she was furios and told she would report me to the
authorities, so I told her to stuff it, and be glad she still was alive. Anyway,
her career was soon over, dream-movies has no use for thirty old women
unfortunately. But I had to admit, her travel hadnt gone as planned, she was some
sixty LY from her destination.

I filled my ship with fuel and left the station. My crew noticed my rather grumpy
mood, and cheered my up with a collage of the latest 50 kills. I smiled at them,
and soon we were happy.

As we exited, I quickly targeted the first cruiser. And fired the front gun. One
second it was there, a mile long battle-ship, the next nothing but burnt metal
and depressurised body-parts. My crew cheered, but a klaxon sounded an incoming
radio-message. 'Piracy and murder cant be tolerated, 10.000 credits in fine'.
Hmm, I had 200 Mcredits, no problem. I lined up my ship against the second
cruiser. By now, cops were leaving the spacestation, but they seemed very bad
pilots, they either chrashed in the space-station or their neighbour, but
ofcourse some managed to get away. I fired the second time. The last of the
cruiser disappeared.

Quickly my Panther Clipper turned 180 degrees and started a continous deadly
plasma beam at the incoming police-ships. Pof, pof! They went down one after the
another. Soon noone remained. My hull had been reduced to 78 percent, but quickly
repaired itself. Now it was the space-stations time. I fired a five minutes
barrage at the hexgon shaped station. Nothing happended except that I was fined
another time for the same amount. How devastating.

Bored at seing the spacestation taking hit after hit, I payed the fine and
entered the space-station. Noone mentioned to me that I've just killed 20 of
their ships and two cruiser, they seemed very neutral they did. We tanked, used
the recreation and I spent 10 Mcredits on some obscure organisation. Shame they
dont have casinoes on the spacestations, easy way to win some (or loose).

We left shortly after.

Stig, Average, Panther Clipper w/what's in the manual, and 192 Mcredits.


